            "shortcode": "DW6ArJMjds8",
            "caption": "ZARA SRPLS \u2013 CLLCTN 16 / DROP I \n\nIn kidswear, this widening is expressed through proportion and a refined approach to utility. Silhouettes are set and specific, holding their shape while remaining easy to wear. In the first drop, colour-blocked looks - such as a bright green trouser with a crisp blue top and neutral jacket - create clear, graphic outlines. In the second, that clarity diffuses: a striped dress with a generous patch pocket balances softness with structure. Across both, soft cottons, considered finishes, and robust construction support comfort and independence.\n\nCreative Director: Karl Templer #karltempler\nPhotographer: Craig McDean @craigmcdeanstudio\nVideo: Ned Rogers @nedrogers \nStyling: Karl Templer #karltempler\nMake up: Mark Carrasquillo @markcarrasquillo\nHair: Lukas Tralmer @lukastralmer\nSet Designer: Gainsbury&Whiting #gainsburyandwhiting\nCasting Director: Piergiorgio @piergiorgio @dmcasting\nProduction: Gainsbury&Whiting \n\n#zara #zarasrpls",
            "type": "Video",
            "hashtags": [
                "#karltempler",
